# Targetime Partners API Examples
# Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@prodUrl = https://crmbackend.becoming-more.pro

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get Session
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/session

### Get KPIs
GET {{baseUrl}}/overview/kpis

### Get Welcome Clients
GET {{baseUrl}}/clients/welcome

### Get Retargeting Clients
GET {{baseUrl}}/clients/retargeting

### Get Follow-up Clients
GET {{baseUrl}}/clients/followups

### Create Welcome Client
POST {{baseUrl}}/clients/welcome
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "status": "active"
}

### Send Retargeting Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/clients/retargeting/1/email-logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "We miss you! Come back and see what's new",
  "content": "Hi there! We noticed you haven't visited us in a while..."
}

### Get Appointments
GET {{baseUrl}}/appointments

### Get Appointments with Filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/appointments?status=scheduled&start_date=2024-01-01

### Create Appointment
POST {{baseUrl}}/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "client_name": "Jane Smith",
  "starts_at": "2024-01-15T10:00:00Z",
  "status": "scheduled",
  "value": 150.00
}

### Export Appointments as CSV
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/export?entity=appointments&format=csv

### Export Clients as JSON
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/export?entity=welcome&format=json

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
